author: @passintogracegoldenyearnin6310

text:
They were unable to travel to perform the normal body tuning process in Japan, so there are ongoing requests and updates being processed. For example Gura's tail and her shoulders have improved by a lot. Ame has been getting more physics but they didn't have collision sorted out in time for the recording. This event was not able to use the studio in Japan, so they had to record motion data and produce composite animations. Kanauru was brought in to clean up the motion data, supply additional animations and composite the final 3D. All of the 3D portion of the event was a series of recordings rendered in Kanauru's animation software, that's why it has his style of shaders. Unless maybe Amelia or someone else inside Hololive needed to import Kanauru's scene data and try to add the official 3D models themselves......it really depends whether Cover allowed an outside contractor to access the model data. This was literally the first time anyone in Hololive did things this way, due to not being able to use the normal studio assets.

There's no way the VRchat engine could handle anything like this, last I checked.

text:
I just came from a clip someone posted of 30:13. I was a fan of you both before, you both especially when it comes to Hololive. Calli was the first clip I can remember of that I saw of a Vtuber and You Gura was the first one I really started watching. But now. Now I’m in love lol. You can call me an official Shrimp and Dead Beat. Anything Card Captor Related is literally the way to my heart. A cover of Catch You Catch Me especially. I thought the clip when I first saw the thumbnail and when it started was a fake. A fan made mmd, but your voices were unmistakable and so I check the links. It was most likely recommended to me because I kept playing a playlist of Calli’s songs. Q especially. That and YouTube probably saw in my history how I used to keep looking up Catch You Catch Me videos in English, Japanese and German. Either way, I was a fan of both your works before. But now like the other Shrimps and Dead Beats. I can say I’m officially in love.

This is kinda weird because I just recently started calling Calli, Dad or Daddy for the memes… Am I the mom in this parasocial relationship?

No wait- that’s Kiara.

text: Hey man just wanna tell you you’re not alone in experiencing pain… everyone does and if they havent, they will. People may be temporary on this Earth, but memories last forever.
author: @wrathcyber

text: @wrathcyber  Thanks man. You're a total stranger to me, but for right now, I'm glad for the sympathy. Never thought I'd ever want anyone's sympathy, but man, losing somebody who makes up like, almost a quarter of your whole world really changes a guy like me. To say it's been rought would be a sever understatement. So, thank you again.
author: @psycholuigiman

text: @psycholuigiman  I hope your doing okay man, I lost a sister a ways back and its rough for everybody. The guy who caused her death is still living free in this very town for years now because the court case hasnt made any progress for just as long. Anyway my point is that there's something indescribable about Gura that just....makes you feel better. Something about her singing and adorkable antics Idk and I hope you have something like that too, that can warm your heart and ease your pain each day.
author: @Rar830

text: @Rar830  Wow. That's gotta be one of the saddest things I've heard in a while. Like, at least my dad died of a health complication. Granted, it was very sudden, and we're still not totally sure why it happened, but it was really a blameless death. I dunno how my mom or bro or I would handle it if he was killed and the killer wasn't quickly dealt with. Forget about me. I'm certainly doing better than when I made my original post. I hope YOU'RE okay. I don't think anything anybody could say, least of all me, could bring real peace and closure to your situation. I guess you're right though. We've got Gura and the rest of Hololive too at least. If nothing else, they'll make us feel better sometimes. I wish you luck and hope that you live a life your sister would be proud of you for.
author: @psycholuigiman

text: @psycholuigiman  Thanks, I cant guarantee I can live a life she would proud of, but I can at least try to be happy or something. I've discovered thats not the easiest thing ever though.
author: @Rar830

text: @Rar830  So true. It's okay to not be happy sometimes though. Sometimes, it just hits you hard. You see a certain thing, or hear a certain sound, or catch a sniff of a certain smell and it just comes to the front of your mind. Apparently, it's like that for a lot of folks for a very long time. Somebody who lost their husband told me after I had gotten home from the funeral "It's okay if you're not okay." Keeping that in mind has sorta made it easier to not try so hard to move on quickly. I encourage you, or anybody who feels that certain sadness one feels from thinking about lost loved ones, to remember that it is okay if you're not okay.
author: @psycholuigiman

text: @psycholuigiman  My mom in particular has talked a bunch about getting over it and accepting her death, moving on and on. So I might quote you.
author: @Rar830

text: @Rar830  Be my guest. Ever since my dad passed, I've been doing a lot of reading on the subject of grief. Everybody seems to grieve in their own way for their own amount of time before kinda getting back to a regular routine. Even after they get back to their routine though, it seems like a lot of folks will still have those days. It really isn't anything to be ashamed of. Especially if you're still able to function and take care of yourself.
author: @psycholuigiman

text: @psycholuigiman  Thanks for all the advice
author: @Rar830

text: Hot take: This is one of the (if not THE) best live celebrations out of Hololive, in my opinion. Especially considering the whole thing was orchestrated by a few people, versus a large Hololive crew working on their live events. While this wasn't exactly "live",  Kanauru's direction and cinematography gave this event an equal, or in some aspects, higher production quality than other live events done by a huge company, whether pre-recorded or not. Regardless, despite the difficulties and the current C situation, Gura and HoloEN as a whole overcame every obstacle and showed us something truly wonderful!

text: It's just amazing to think about someone growing up, literally pursuing this dream when it wasn't yet popular or even viable as a career (let's be honest, Gura didn't accidentally sign up to be a hololive creator for the fun chance, this is her life long passion) through time and perseverance honing their skill, timing, and delivery goofing around with friends, then by uploading videos that get watched by family and friends before becoming steadily more popular until one day they hit virtual gold, serendipitously or otherwise, then springboard that into 4 million fans a few years later as a culmination of a life's journey (it's just getting started, but "the story so far" kinda way). Could you imagine being her (and the others) literally living the dream or their parents watching this? Fucking crazy cool.

text:
Why does Hololive insist on making Hololive ENGLISH sing a bunch of Japanese songs during their 3D concerts (and mostly making Japanese songs for their individual releases, besides Calli who writes her own songs)? Is the audience for Hololive English Japanese speakers or English speakers? I don't have a problem with Japanese songs fundamentally, but it's just always weird that whenever allowed to choose the songs they sing, Hololive English mostly goes with English songs with a few Japanese ones sprinkled in (usually anime or Hololive songs), but every time there's a big production it's almost wall-to-wall Japanese.

Good concert, but I do not understand this.

text:
There's a reason why their karaokes are unarchived, because the Western music corporations will strike down any channel that has their music online. The fact this video still remains archived is because they're singing japanese songs, which have different copyright laws. 

I don't deny EN has been producing more JP original songs than EN but that's because they dont have music contacts within the English industry and have to reply on their their company (Japanese/Jpop orientated) to help them look. Gura has mentioned she wants to produce an EN song though, so just sit tight.
